## Installation

### 1. Install the plugin

```bash
npm install @better-auth-extended/{{name}}
```

### 2. Add the plugin to your auth config

To use the {{titleCase name}} plugin, add it to your auth config.

```ts
import { betterAuth } from "better-auth";
import { {{camelCase name}} } from "@better-auth-extended/{{name}}";

export const auth = betterAuth({
    // ... other configuration options
    plugins: [{{camelCase name}}()],
});
```

### 3. Add the client plugin

Include the {{titleCase name}} client plugin in your authentication client instance.

```ts
import { createAuthClient } from "better-auth/client";
import { {{camelCase name}}Client } from "@better-auth-extended/{{name}}/client";

const authClient = createAuthClient({
    plugins: [{{camelCase name}}Client()],
});
```

### 4. Run migrations

```bash
npx @better-auth/cli migrate
```

or generate

```bash
npx @better-auth/cli generate
```

